manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MADE TO LAST You can count on a Five Star Advance Notebook throughout the year. Our high-quality paper helps keep notes clear and neat, while our ultra-durable, water-resistant covers protect your writing from wear, tear and spills. STUDY ANYWHERE, ANYTIME Studying just got a whole lot easier. The Five Star app and our specially-designed paper make it easy to scan, study and organize your notes wherever you go! Use the app to create instant digital flashcards, track your study progress, and study anywhere, anytime. CUSTOMIZABLE SECTIONS Create a notebook that works best for you! Our movable tabbed dividers let you rearrange within the notebook, are color-coded for easy visibility and have a double-sided storage pocket that expands to hold loose sheets and assignments. ORGANIZE YOUR WAY Keep your notebooks clearly organized. Five Star Advance Notebooks have a durable Spiral Guard spine to protect the notebook binding, plus a writable label so you can quickly identify which notebook you need in your locker or backpack.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for college
reviews.reviewText: I'm a college student in my 40s and I still like to write notes by hand. This is great for keeping all my notes separate for each class and I love that there is a folder in the dividers. I use the folders for the lab handouts I get for my classes. It is a pretty thick notebook, so keep that in mind. I wasn't expecting it to be this thick and it takes up a bit of room in my rolling backpack, but I will be reusing it each quarter so it's a good investment. The removable dividers will make it easy to use again next quarter so I can keep some relevant notes and just move the divider down to the next blank pages. Overall, a great product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 13, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: Bought the cheapest colour and was not disappointed
reviews.reviewText: I had a similar notebook during high school and I wanted to have one once again at uni. The price difference between teal and red was ridiculous (~£7) but, honestly, the notebook is the same.In general, the notebook is great if you take various subjects a day and have a folder at home where you actually sort the pages into coherence. If you want a single notebook for year-round activities it does have some flaws: you cant add new pages, the sectioning is limited and its uncomfortably bulky to use outside the table/seat scheme (e.g. field trips, those baby chair seats universities love, labs or practicals). I don't recommend carrying this along a laptop or other bulky things since its HEAVY, my back has not forgiven me.Overall a 4/5 for what I intended it for, for more versatility it could however be substituted by a folder and refill pages so 3/5.
